3. The loop starts from the last index (length - 1) of the input string down to the first index (0). This helps in adding each character of the input string to the new `revStr` variable in reverse order.
4. Finally, a Toast message is displayed with the reversed string by calling `Toast.makeText(context, revStr, Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show()`.

