A NullPointerException (NPE) is a runtime exception that occurs when your program tries to access a null reference or invoke a method on a null object. Here are some common causes of NPEs in Java:

1. Dereferencing a null reference: When you try to access a field or method of an object that has not been initialized or is null, you will get an NPE. For example:
```java
String str = null;
System.out.println(str.length()); // NPE!
```
2. Passing a null parameter to a method: If a method expects a non-null parameter and you pass null instead, you can get an NPE. For example:
```java
public void printName(String name) {
    System.out.println(name); // NPE if name is null!
}

// ...
printName(null); // NPE!
```
3. Using the wrong type of object: If you try to use a method on an object that is not of the correct type, you can get an NPE. For example:
```java
Integer x = 10;
String y = "hello";
System.out.println(x.toString()); // OK
System.out.println(y.length()); // NPE!
```
4. Trying to access a field or method of an object that has been garbage collected: If you try to access an object that has been garbage collected, you can get an NPE. For example:
```java
String str = "hello";
System.out.println(str.length()); // OK
str = null;
System.gc(); // Garbage collection
System.out.println(str.length()); // NPE!
```
To fix NPEs, you should:

1. Check for null references before dereferencing them. For example:
```java
if (str != null) {
    System.out.println(str.length());
} else {
    System.out.println("str is null!");
}
```
2. Use the correct type of object when calling methods. For example:
```java
String str = "hello";
System.out.println(str.length()); // OK
int x = 10;
System.out.println(x.toString()); // NPE!
```
3. Avoid dereferencing null objects in the first place by using defensive programming techniques, such as:
	* Null-checking method arguments before using them.
	* Initializing objects to non-null values before using them.
	* Using the Optional class to encapsulate nullable references and avoid null pointer exceptions.

